El Perro Del Mar was founded in the end of 2003 around the idea and need 
of making music on terms of one's own. Behind the alter-ego is the sole member Sarah Assbring. 
El Perro Del Mar started out as an mp3-artist and in spring 2004 the first cdr-ep 'Baby, I've been in a bad place' was released by the Swedish label Hybris. The two following cdr-ep:s, 'I've got good news' and 'Holiday Special', were released shortly thereafter.
